Mathare United coach Francis Kimanzi is the Fidelity Insurance Coach of the Month for January. Kimanzi, whose side were top of the league the entire month of January, wade off competition from Bandari's Bernard Mwalala and Western Stima's Paul Ogai. During the month of January, Kimanzi led Mathare to four wins and two draws from six matches. Mathare United were held by Gor Mahia and Kariobangi Sharks while they beat Kakamega Homeboyz, Vihiga United, KCB and Tusker. This is the third time the Harambee Stars assistant coach is walking away with the award, having won the inaugural gong in February 2016 and also named the best in February 2018. More to follow...  